# Styling and Design System Patterns

RYLA uses TailwindCSS 4 with custom design tokens. Design system based on purple/pink gradient theme. Components use `@ryla/ui` design tokens and variants. CVA (class-variance-authority) for component variants. Radix UI primitives with TailwindCSS styling.

## Requirements

### Design Tokens

- Use design tokens from `@ryla/ui` design system
- Prefer CSS variables over hardcoded values
- Use semantic color names (primary, accent, text, border)
- Follow spacing scale (4px grid system)
- Use typography tokens for consistent text styling

### TailwindCSS Patterns

- Use utility classes for styling
- Prefer composition over custom CSS
- Use responsive variants (sm:, md:, lg:)
- Use dark mode variants when applicable
- Keep class names organized and readable

### Component Variants

- Use CVA for component variants
- Define variants in component files
- Export variant types for type safety
- Use consistent variant naming

### Color System

- Primary: Purple gradient theme (`#A855F7`, `#9333EA`)
- Accent: Pink/orange (`#EC4899`, `#F472B6`)
- Background: Dark theme (`#0A0A0B`, `#111113`)
- Text: White with opacity variants
- Borders: Subtle white with opacity

