### Component Styling Pattern

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Component with variants and className merge
import { cn } from '@ryla/ui/utils';

interface CardProps {
  variant?: 'default' | 'elevated' | 'outline';
  className?: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Card({ variant = 'default', className, children }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div
      className={cn(
        'rounded-lg p-4',
        {
          'bg-background-elevated': variant === 'default',
          'bg-background-elevated shadow-lg': variant === 'elevated',
          'bg-transparent border border-border': variant === 'outline',
        },
        className
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

- Design tokens - Always use design tokens, never hardcode colors/spacing
- Utility classes - Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Responsive - Use mobile-first responsive design
- Variants - Use CVA for component variants
- Consistency - Follow spacing scale and typography tokens
- Accessibility - Include focus states and proper contrast
- Performance - Use Tailwind's purging for production builds
- Organization - Keep class names organized and readable

